Description: We are a Washington, DC, digital communications firm that specializes in video-driven campaigns for associations and corporations.
Headquarters Regions: Washington DC Metro Area, Southern US
Full Description: LAI Video specializes in video-centric campaigns to get the word out. The kind of campaigns that attract action, create change or make something matter. Whether you’re educating a targeted group of movers-and-shakers or raising awareness to the masses, we help you write your story, tell it and roll it out. Before we become storytellers, we investigate. We get to know our partners and the pending problem. We determine demographics. Sling together sounds. Pitch prose. Invent idioms. We establish a hook — a hashtag — so irresistible that we can draw the right eyeballs, but also deliver a satisfying tale.  Next, we build out the basic structure for the campaign. A backbone. Is this a pre-roll video ad? A meaty, content-rich series? Does it live on a freshly-developed microsite or operate within an existing communication strategy? What are all of the social trappings and tweets to tease the messaging? Our team of creative producers and wordsmiths wrap your message with a solid script. Something that cuts through the spam of a typical inbox and sounds like it was written by a gosh-dang-it human being. Something that’s well-researched but carries with it a strong sense of self or humor. It has all the right feels and is inherently memorable. Well-versed in design, cinematography and motion graphics, our team of nerds will convert your campaign blueprint into something wonderful. Something totally planned, but completely organic. Something unexpected. Our Producer + Project Managers shepherd the campaign through production, keeping your products punctual while ensuring exquisite craftsmanship. When the deliverables are ready to roll, we release them to the world (or specific parts of the world). Following a controlled timeline, we invade the airwaves, socialwaves and any kind of waves that will make the biggest splash. We evaluate the initial response to grow the campaign and best adapt our approach for the next project. We hold back tears (the good kind) as we wrap-up a well-done work — something we hope you appreciate and hope we can blog about later.
Industry Groups: Media and Entertainment, Sales and Marketing, Video

Description: Amazing websites for contractors.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Contractor Gorilla makes amazing websites for construction contractors. Their website services are unique and they come up with a custom solution for all their contractor websites. They focus on creating a web solution that can deliver results. What you WON’T get at Contractor Gorilla is a generic templated website, a one size fits all website, keyword stuffed web pages and bad design. IDENTITY: This is the core of your online marketing and will guide the strategy from your logo to your letterhead. When we work on creating your identity/persona, we look at your ideal customer, your company objectives and other aspects related to your business. When we've finished creating your identity, you’ll have a strong vision for the look and feel of your contractor website. DESIGN: Appearance greatly influences peoples perceptions, and we use this proven model when designing websites. Our websites our deigned with function and usability at the forefront. The goal is to make a lasting impression on your website visitors. Good design is something people remember. It excites website visitors and stimulates their mind. Your website should help visitors visualize how your services can meet their needs. FUNCTION: Your website needs to inspire confidence in your company and if it doesn't function how it should visitors will get frustrated. We make sure that all media loads correct, there’s no broken links and every click works the way it should. We test websites on all common browsers and make sure it looks good on mobile and tablets. CONTENT: Have you ever heard the saying “content is king”? This is something we strongly believe in and work on when creating your website. Content can be created in many forms but for contractors having the basics is essential. We recommend photo galleries of work, how-to articles, testimonials and blogging about relevant topics. MARKETING: Now that you've created an amazing identity, have an engaging website with valuable content, it’s time to be found. People aren't going to start visiting your website just because it’s online. We can help you explore different marketing options and develop a strategy that meets your budget.
